                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem><para>JPA performance pitfalls</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <note>
            <title></title>
            <para>The material in this paper is geared towards developers working with 
                SQL and JPA. The topic of performance is much larger than the scope 
                covered here and should involve DBAs, Hardware Engineers, etc. when
                working through the complete solution. However, the material covered 
                in this paper should be an excellent start for developers to better 
                understand what costs what, how you can better know when there are
                issues or success, and where to look for solutions. Some topics were
                purposely left out to help concentrate on the primary scenarios.</para>
        </note>
    </preface>

